Apple Health Integration
WorkoutAI integrates with Apple Health to enable secure, context-driven data exchange between your Health app and our Service. With your explicit consent, WorkoutAI can both read and write the following health metrics:
Exercise Data:
Records of your physical activities that help track workouts and progress.
Total Calories Burned:
The cumulative energy expenditure during activities, used to monitor your fitness outcomes.
Height:
Your recorded height, essential for tailoring health insights and personal recommendations.
Weight:
Your weight information, which is crucial for tracking changes and optimizing workout plans.
Body Fat Percentage:
Data reflecting your body composition, used to assess overall health and fitness progress.
We request access to these metrics only when needed—such as during a weight entry or profile update—to ensure our requests are clearly related to the current context. Standard Apple permission dialogs provide clear explanations for these data requests, and you can manage your permissions at any time in Settings > Privacy > Health.
All health data is handled with the utmost care and protected using industry-standard security measures. We only access your data with your permission, ensuring your privacy and trust remain our highest priority.
Service Providers
We may employ third party companies and individuals to facilitate our Service ("Service Providers"), to provide the Service on our behalf, to perform Service-related services or to assist us in analyzing how our Service is used.
These third parties have access to your data only to perform these tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.
Links To Other Sites
Our Service may contain links to other sites that are not operated by us. If you click on a third party link, you will be directed to that third party's site. We strongly advise you to review the Privacy Policy of every site you visit.
We have no control over and assume no responsibility for the content, privacy policies or practices of any third party sites or services.
Children's Privacy
Our Service does not address anyone under the age of 18 ("Children").
We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from anyone under the age of 18. If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your Children has provided us with data, please contact us. If we become aware that we have collected data from children without verification of parental consent, we take steps to remove that information from our servers.
Data Sharing for Refund Management
We may collect and share consumption data related to your use of the app with Apple’s App Store Server to process refund requests. This includes:

Time spent using the app, 
Content accessed or completed, 
Lifetime purchase history and usage frequency, 
Previous refund history (if applicable). 
This data is shared securely and only when required to assist in refund decisions initiated through Apple’s App Store.
Changes To This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
We will update the "effective date" at the top of this Privacy Policy.
You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.
